Holiday travel is stressful enough these days, but if you're planning to travel by air any time from Thanksgiving through New Year's, prepare for fuller-than-ever planes and the usual security rigmarole. The TSA is still updating its travel tips due to the recent government shutdown, but "nothing will be dramatically different this year," an agency official tells us; an expansion of the permitted items list was put on hold earlier last spring amid controversy over its aborted  plan to allow small knives in carry-ons . But you're probably worried less about that carving knife for turkey dinner than some benign-sounding holiday items. So remember a few things when you're packing up for grandma's house: More from  Cond√© Nast Traveler :